U.S. Secretary of State GeorgeShultz said the Marines spy case had cast a "heavy shadow" overhis scheduled talks in Moscow next week.    "Unfortunately, as is so often the case when we are in themidst of potentially promising discussions with the Soviets,the discussions take place in a difficult environment generatedby their actions, and these things cast a heavy shadow on ourdiscussions," he told reporters. Reuter&#3;